column2: Skip Groff and Rick Springfield, circa 1972
column7: A photograph circa 1972 of musician and actor Rick Springfield with Washington, D.C.-area disc jockey Skip Groff. Springfield was visiting Groff's radio station, WINX AM in Rockville, Maryland, to promote his current album, "Beginnings." Groff went on to be the owner of Yesterday & Today Records, a record store in Rockville that was central to the rock and punk music scenes in the Washington, D.C. area from 1977 to 2002.

column2: Psychiana, A Mail Order Religion Created in the Small Town of Moscow, Idaho
column7: Short video describing Psychiana, a mail order religion that preached the New Thought Movement. In 1928, Dr. Frank B. Robinson created Psychiana in Moscow, Idaho.

column7: This radio program corresponds with the transcript of Radio Psychiana - Series for Dr. Frank B. Robinson No. 3. Episode begins proclaiming the growth of Pyschiana and then takes listeners to Robinson's home in Moscow, Idaho, describing its appearance. A dialogue begins between a 'guide' and Robinson about miracles, healing, the God-Law, the mail Robinson receives, and the 'Life Impulse' or 'motivating spirit' that allows people to think and live with God.

column7: This radio program episode discusses man's quest for answers, then introduces Robinson and his concept of the Cosmic God-Power. Robinson discusses the God-Power, reads a student letter asking for help, and uses the discovery of the 'cosmic ray' by Professor Milikan as evidence that there is invisible power around us. Robinson claims this Power is for our use and can bring anyone what they desire. Also includes a testimonial from a man claimed to live in Holland.

column2: Good News - Purpose of the Program
column7: This radio program episode outlines the purpose of the 'Good News' radio program, to broadcast positive and peaceful things rather than negative. Episode includes organ music and songs sung by Al Marino, jokes made in the face of war, and urges listeners to buy quality-made products for better piece of mind.
